main event: A civilian observed a group of lights in Saginaw, Minnesota on November 5, 1966.
interesting points: The lights were described as white, yellow, orange, and blue in color,The lights moved rapidly and could vanish when looked away from, The observer noted the object was brighter than any star and larger than Venus, There was no physical evidence left behind by the lights, Many other people in the area reported similar sightings around the same time.
